      "writtenOn": "2016-06-14T12:21:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We used \"...\" and __VA_ARGS__ to reduce the line length of type variations. Replacing it with arguments will exceed 80 column limit for macros with more number of arguments and will be somewhat messy.\n\nFor e.g.\nBelow variation has 6 arguments.\n#define ILVR_D2_UB(...) ILVR_D2(v16u8, __VA_ARGS__)\n\nAfter the change it will look like, \n#define ILVR_D2_UB(in0, in1, in2, in3, out0, out1)  \\\n        ILVR_D2(v16u8, in0, in1, in2, in3, out0, out1)",
